# Home Assistant Naming Convention & Entity Rename Plan

## Convention Rules

### 1. Language
- All English — no Dutch (rolluik, slaapkamer, deken, keuken, thuis, schuif pui, etc.)

### 2. Friendly Name Format
- Title Case everywhere
- Pattern: [Area] [Device/Thing] [Attribute] — most-general to most-specific, left to right
- Area prefix only when needed to disambiguate
- Never repeat what the domain already tells you

### 3. Automation Format
- Pattern: [Area]. [Device]. [Action]
- Example: "Bedroom. Cover. Open and close" ✓

### 4. Helper Format
- Descriptive noun/adjective phrase in Title Case
- No underscores or dashes in friendly names

### 5. What NOT to include in friendly names
- Integration slugs (no "shelly-keuken", "valetudo_illustrioussickpheasant")
- Raw hex addresses (no "0xa4c138b244f6fe12")
- Device model numbers (no "Varin® VA-E002")

